sortProperties.markdownDescription:
**_SORT PROPERTIES_**

_This option will alphabetically sort object properties (keys). This can be an expensive operation when dealing with large objects with over 2k properties._

---
#### Before&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
When disabled, ie: `false` properties will not be sorted.
```css
.class {
  width: 100px;
  color: blue;
  font-size: 20px;
  background: pink
}

```

---

#### After&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;üëé
When set to `true` all properties are alphanumerically sorted
```json

.class {
  color: blue;
  background: pink;
  font-size: 20px;
  width: 100px;
}

```

braceAllman.markdownDescription:
**_BRACE ALLMAN_**

_Determines if opening curly braces will exist on the same line as their condition or be forced onto a new line. The formatting structure is known as [Allman](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indentation_style#Allman_style) style indentation_.

---

#### Disabled&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;üëé
Below is an example when this option is set to `false` and each object in the array starts curly braces inline.
```json

[
  { "prop": "value" },
  { "prop": "value" },
  { "prop": "value" }
]

```
---
#### Enabled&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;üëç
Below is an example when this option is set to `true` and each object in the array starts on a newline.
```json

[
  {
    "prop": "value"
  },
  {
    "prop": "value"
  },
  {
    "prop": "value"
  }
]

```

bracePadding.markdownDescription:
**_BRACE PADDING_**

_The `bracePadding` rule will insert newlines at the top and bottom of nested properties._

---
#### Disabled&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;üëç
Below is an example when this option is set to `true`
```json

{
 "one": {
    "xx": {
      "xx": false
    }
  }
}

```

---

#### Enabled&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;üëé
Below is an example when this option is set to `false`
```json

{
 "one": {

    "xx": {

      "xx": false

    }

  }
}

```

